@sk8rdude461 wrote:

The first error in the file is because you need to make a method public.

find:

in your moneypouch.java

And change it to ‘public’ void.

The rest of your errors are because you are trying to make an object an int that won’t directly convert to an int.

item.title: Money Pouch Error
item.dc:creator: @Runecessor Runecessor
item.description:
@Runecessor wrote:

I hope you do understand you can not just post something this broad and expect an answer. These errors could be caused by many things, for one to determine what the cause of these errors are said individual would/ will have to look at the command line of each error. It is not as simple as posting your errors and saying “Help me with my problems” it would also serve you better if you left a list of things you did to try and resolve the problem or the original problem that when fixed triggered a new series of errors. More than likely one of you screwed something up when you “fixed” those bagillion errors you claim to have originally had. Another thing is seeing that these errors seem to involve the money pouch mainly there is probably a bad code that if fixed it would fix everything else.
